Imagine a vector which is perpendicular to a plane. Now, a forrce might also act on that plane in particular directions

Therefore, total possible vector orientations perpendicular to the plane (which in turn also  represents all possible orientations in which the plane itself can exist): 3 (along,x,y,z)
Also, total possible Force vector orientations perpendicular to the plave: 3 (along,x,y,z)

So total possible orientations of the system: 3*3=9

Thus each of the 9 elements in the matix represents basis vectors along the direction of various combinations of plane orientation vector and the force vector 


This matrix can thus be createwd using the Kronecker product of 2 Vectors 


we can extend it to higher ranked vectors as well
  

